# Git Commit Message Format

**Mandatory** for every commit in this repository.

## Format

```text
FP-<N>: <short summary>
```

| Part | Rule |
|------|------|
| `FP-<N>` | Task id from tracker (e.g. `FP-3`). Uppercase `FP`, hyphen, digits only. |
| `:` | Single colon + one space after task id |
| Summary | Short imperative summary in English (or Russian if user prefers — match recent commits); no period at end; ≤ 72 chars total line preferred |

## Examples

```text
FP-3: close Sprint 0 documentation
FP-12: add match feed mock data
FP-1: fix energy distribution on manual style
```

## Invalid (do not use)

```text
close Sprint 0                    # missing task id
FP-3 close Sprint 0             # missing colon
FP-3:                           # empty summary
[FP-3] close Sprint 0           # wrong prefix format
FP-3: close Sprint 0.           # trailing period (avoid)
```

## Agent workflow

- Ask user for task id (`FP-N`) if unknown before committing.
- Never commit without the `FP-<N>:` prefix unless user explicitly overrides for this one commit.
- Use HEREDOC for `git commit -m` to preserve formatting.
